# .mission-control/.gitignore
#
# By default, ignore everything in .mission-control/ to keep mission state,
# logs, and transient data out of version control.
#
# Teams can selectively whitelist directories and files they want to share
# across the team by uncommenting (or adding) negation patterns below.

# Ignore everything by default
*

# Always keep this .gitignore
!.gitignore

# ─── Team-Shared Configuration ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment to share project-level settings with your team:
# !settings.md

# ─── Playbooks ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment to share custom playbooks (reusable mission templates):
# !playbooks/
# !playbooks/**

# ─── Mission Memory ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment to share learnings extracted from past missions:
# !memory/
# !memory/**

# ─── Selective Memory Sharing ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Alternatively, share only high-confidence learnings by pattern:
# !memory/gotcha-*.md
# !memory/pattern-*.md

# ─── Things You Should Almost Never Commit ────────────────────────────────────
# Active mission state (transient, session-specific):
#   missions/active.json
#
# Mission archive (can be very large over time):
#   missions/archive/
#
# Mission logs (transient):
#   missions/log.jsonl
